comments: McDaniels (PHI) cleanly dislodges the ball from Jokic (DEN).
Springer (PHI) and Caldwell-Pope (DEN) come together at the same spot on the floor and marginal contact occurs as they pursue the loose ball.
Murray (DEN) is turning away from Springer (PHI) and marginal contact occurs as Springer passes the ball.
Caldwell-Pope (DEN) is already in Harrell's (PHI) path and absorbs the contact during the screen.
Milton (PHI) slides his arm across Caldwell-Pope's (DEN) front and the contact is marginal.
Jokic (DEN) is already in Springer's (PHI) path when contact occurs and he does not deliver contact.
Harrell (PHI) is moving alongside Jokic's (DEN) path and marginal contact occurs during the drive.
McDaniels (PHI) legally contests Porter Jr.'s (DEN) jump shot attempt.
Harrell (PHI) legally contests Caldwell-Pope's (DEN) tip-in attempt at the basket.
Caldwell-Pope (DEN) steps slightly forward towards Milton (PHI) and marginal contact occurs on the perimeter.
Milton (PHI) is bracing for the contact from Caldwell-Pope (DEN) and marginal contact occurs as Milton releases away from the contact.
Jokic (DEN) brings his hand down and makes contact with Harrell's (PHI) arm as he defends the driving shot attempt.
Green (DEN) is already in Milton's (PHI) path when contact occurs and he does not deliver contact.
Milton (PHI) rests his hand on Jokic's (DEN) side during the drive and the contact is marginal.
Harrell (PHI) brushes Green's (DEN) arm as he defends the shot near the rim, and the contact is marginal.
Springer (PHI) legally contests Green's (DEN) shot near the rim.
Jokic (DEN) legally contests Kormaz's (PHI) driving shot attempt.
Green (DEN) is already in Milton's (PHI) path when contact occurs and he does not deliver contact.

Korkmaz (PHI) moves laterally into Murray's (DEN) path and he does not establish a legal guarding position prior to contact. However, Murray should have not been deemed to have established frontcourt status, and Denver should have inbounded the ball in the back court with 24 seconds on the shot clock and not in the frontcourt with 16 on the shot clock.
Murray (DEN) legally receives the inbound pass in the backcourt.
Springer (PHI) is moving alongside Murray's (DEN) path and marginal contact occurs during the drive.
McDaniels (PHI) is in the paint for less than three seconds when he is imminently exiting.
Harrell (PHI) legally contests Green's (DEN) jump shot attempt.
Porter Jr. (DEN) legally contests Springer's (PHI) driving shot attempt.
Harrell (PHI) makes contact with the ball while it is still in the imaginary cylinder above the rim.
Green (DEN) legally contests Harrell's (PHI) put-back attempt at the basket.
Green (DEN) has his heel on the line when he receives the pass and an out of bounds violation should have been called.

The foul call on McDaniels (PHI) for contact with Green (DEN) was reviewed via a PHI coach's challenge and deemed unsuccessful since McDaniels clearly and conclusively made contact with part of Green's hand/wrist that was not in contact with the ball during his shot attempt. The missed out of bounds call was not reviewable by rule because it did not occur just prior to the foul.
Jokic (DEN) and Harrell (PHI) engage and disengage away from the ball and the contact is marginal.
Harrell (PHI) is already in Caldwell-Pope's (DEN) path when contact occurs and does not deliver contact.
Caldwell-Pope (DEN) places his hand momentarily on Harrell's (PHI) hip as they disengage following the pick.
Korkmaz (PHI) brushes Murray's (DEN) arm and marginal contact occurs as Murray secures the rebound.
